  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "We use HTTP(S) in different parts of Hardhat, and some parts of it are scattered across different parts of the codebase. This is not ideal, and has already brought some problems. For example, we had to implement support for proxies more than once.\r\n\r\nWe should instead have a single module that takes responsibility for all of our HTTP(S)-client needs.\r\n\r\nAlso, while we are at it, we should move away from node-fetch, probably to [unidici](https://undici.nodejs.org).",
